Wouldn't it be a bit nicer like this instead?

```
    if (exc && PyErr_ExceptionMatches(PyExc_OverflowError))
    {
      PyErr_Clear();
      pc->PyTypeToJSON = PyLongToUINT64;
      tc->type = JT_ULONG;
      GET_TC(tc)->unsignedLongValue = PyLong_AsUnsignedLongLong(obj);

      exc = PyErr_Occurred();
